	<h2>Supplies Checklist</h2>
	<p>Have these on hand for spring maintenance:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>☐ Oxygen bleach or fence cleaner</li>
		<li>☐ Stiff bristle brush</li>
		<li>☐ Garden hose with spray nozzle</li>
		<li>☐ Replacement fasteners (galvanized or stainless)</li>
		<li>☐ Wood stain/sealer (if applicable)</li>
		<li>☐ Brushes or sprayer for staining</li>
		<li>☐ Drop cloths for plant protection</li>
		<li>☐ Lubricant for gate hinges</li>
		<li>☐ Touch-up paint (if applicable)</li>
		<li>☐ Work gloves and safety glasses</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>When to Call a Professional</h2>
	<p>DIY maintenance handles most needs, but call professionals for:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Multiple leaning or damaged posts</li>
		<li>Significant rot or structural damage</li>
		<li>Major sections needing replacement</li>
		<li>Termite or pest infestation</li>
		<li>Gate repairs beyond adjustment</li>
		<li>If you're unsure about the extent of problems</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Creating a Maintenance Calendar</h2>

	<h3>Spring (March-May)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Complete inspection</li>
		<li>Deep cleaning</li>
		<li>Staining/sealing if needed</li>
		<li>Address all repairs</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Summer (June-August)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Monitor for heat damage</li>
		<li>Keep vegetation trimmed</li>
		<li>Adjust sprinklers away from fence</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Fall (September-November)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Quick inspection</li>
		<li>Clear debris</li>
		<li>Minor touch-ups</li>
		<li>Prepare for winter rain</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Winter (December-February)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Inspect after storms</li>
		<li>Address urgent damage</li>
		<li>Plan spring maintenance</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Conclusion</h2>
	<p>Investing a few hours in spring fence maintenance protects your investment and keeps your property looking its best. The mild weather window between winter rain and summer heat is perfect for cleaning, repairs, and protective treatments.</p>

	<p>Regular maintenance extends fence life significantly—a well-maintained fence can last years longer than a neglected one. Make spring fence care an annual tradition, and you'll enjoy a beautiful, functional fence for many years to come.</p>

	<p>Need help with fence maintenance or repairs? Contact us for professional service or a free assessment of your fence's condition.</p>

